	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">mikejmoffitt wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Why did so many [console ports of <em>Pac-Man</em>] use this weirdly shaped maze?</div><br />Because the NTSC screen is not as tall, and the console VDPs had trouble addressing areas smaller than 8x8 pixels, and I guess the various port developers thought players wouldn't prefer a scrolling maze. Or should it have been designed with 4x4 pixel tiles, with a maze only 128 pixels tall? That might have worked for the Game Boy but not elsewhere. Platforms with an all-pixels-addressable screen and without severe attribute clash of the Spectrum could have done 6x6 pixel cells and a 192 pixel maze though.

		

		</td>
